# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# How the three env-related files work (dev local setup)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
#   .env.example  (this file)  →  Committed. Just a template: variable names + hints.
#        ↓ you copy and fill in
#   .env                      →  Not committed. Your real values (secrets, paths).
#        ↑ loaded by
#   .envrc                    →  Committed. One line: "dotenv". Tells direnv:
#                                "when someone cd's here, load .env into the shell."
#
# So: you cd into the project → direnv runs .envrc → .env is loaded → Python
# sees CLIBLE_* in os.environ. No Python package needed to read .env.
#
# Override per environment: dev (.env), test (pytest env), Docker (-e / env_file).
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# CLIBLE_DB_PATH=
# CLIBLE_API_BASE_URL=https://api.bible-api.com
# CLIBLE_TRANSLATIONS=KJV,ESV,NIV
# CLIBLE_DATA_DIR=
# CLIBLE_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=10
# CLIBLE_REQUEST_DELAY=1
